        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Yes. Kit's Newsletter plan is free for up to 10,000 subscribers and includes unlimited landing pages, forms, email broadcasts, and basic automations. You can also sell digital products on the free plan. No credit card required to start.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "How does Kit compare to Mailchimp for creator email marketing?",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Kit was built specifically for creators, while Mailchimp serves a broader market. Kit charges per unique subscriber (not per list), includes native digital product sales, and offers visual automations designed for content-driven businesses. Creators like James Clear and Ali Abdaal use Kit because it handles creator workflows without complexity.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Can I migrate my existing email list to Kit from another platform?",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
